statement.p:
Compute the logarithms.



\log_3 9


\log_5 125 


\log_4 \dfrac{1}{16}


\log_5 \sqrt{5}

webwork.pg-code:
Context(Fraction);
$ya = Compute("-1/3");
$ba = Compute("8");
$xa = Compute("1/2");
$yb = Formula("x");
$bb = Compute("5");
$xb = Compute("46");

Context(Fraction);
$y = Formula("x");
$b = Compute("3");
$x = Compute("90");
$exact = log(90)/log(3);
$answer = Compute("$exact")->with(
  tolType => 'absolute',
  tolerance => .0005,
);

statement.p:
Approximate the following logarithms to 2 decimal places.



\log{6.5}


\log{256}

The value of a large tractor originally worth $30,000 depreciates exponentially according to the formula 
    V(t) = 30,000(10)^{-0.04t} 
where t is in years. When will the tractor be worth half its original value?

